# Vue Rules (extends 00-core.mdc)

## Component Architecture
- Composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">` by default.
- Views: page-level composition. Components: reusable UI. Composables: shared logic.
- One component per `.vue` file. Split if > 200 lines.

## State Management
- Component-local `ref()` / `reactive()` first.
- Composables for shared logic. Pinia only for genuinely shared distant state — record in `docs/decisions.md`.

## Data & Services
- API calls in `services/` — never inline in views or stores.
- Use `defineProps<T>()` and `defineEmits<T>()` with explicit TypeScript types.

## Quality
- Run `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test && npm run build` after changes.
- Use code review checklist in `AGENTS.md` §7 before submitting.


